  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Tax Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Lead and manage a small team of tax professionals across a portfolio of corporate tax clients.</li><li>Oversee the planning, execution, and review of tax engagements to ensure quality and compliance.</li><li>Deliver comprehensive tax advisory and compliance services, including on complex matters such as restructuring and cross-border transactions.</li><li>Act as the engagement lead, responsible for project planning, budgeting, and delivery.</li><li>Collaborate closely with directors on engagement strategy, technical issues, and client management.</li><li>Develop and maintain long-term client relationships, identifying and pursuing new business opportunities.</li><li>Conduct internal and external seminars or training sessions on corporate tax topics.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>A recognized degree in Accountancy or a professional qualification such as ACA, ACCA, CPA Australia, SCTP, or equivalent.</li><li>Minimum of 5 years of relevant experience in corporate tax, preferably with a large or mid-tier international accounting firm.</li><li>Experience with tax assignments in the shipping industry is an added advantage.</li><li>Strong technical knowledge of Singapore corporate tax laws and regulations.</li><li>Excellent communication, interpersonal, and leadership skills.</li><li>Proven ability to manage client relationships and deliver exceptional service.</li></ul><p>If you are looking to take the next step in your tax career with a reputable firm that values professionalism, development, and teamwork, we invite you to apply.</p>",
